      "span_text": "The AUTS2 gene is located on chromosome 7q11.22 and consists of 19 exons, the first 6 exons being separated by very large introns and the last 13 exons being close.  One of these common single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) in the AUTS2 gene is rs6943555, which comprises a single nucleotide change of T to A in intron 4."
